OL,3,CMum of schoolgirl who died at
OL,4,Cpsychiatric unit welcomes new guidance
OL,6,F"Mia should not have had to die for
OL,7,Fchange to happen, because as the Royal
OL,8,FCollege of Psychiatry has said, it is
OL,9,Fhighly treatable condition when
OL,10,Fidentified promptly.
OL,12,F"It is not a new condition, its one
OL,13,Four NHS system has, until now, failed
OL,14,Fto properly train its staff in
OL,15,Fidentifying and treating."
OL,17,FAt the conclusion of the inquest,
OL,18,FNottingham University Hospitals NHS
OL,19,FTrust, which runs the Queen's Medical
OL,20,FCentre, apologised to Mia's family for
OL,21,Fnot identifying her condition.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/6
